'''David Manley''' is an American philosopher specializing in [[metaphysics]], [[philosophy of language]], and [[epistemology]]. He is Associate Professor of [[Philosophy]] at [[the University of Michigan, Ann Arbor]], [[Michigan]].
==Work== *{{cite book |author=John Hawthorne, David Manley |title=The Reference Book |publisher=Oxford University Press|year=2012|isbn=0199693676 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3NMTUqrLk9YC&printsec=frontcover}} *{{cite book |title=Metametaphysics: New Essays on the Foundations of Ontology |editor= D. Chalmers David Manley and Ryan Wasserman |publisher=Oxford University Press |year=2009|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6nqzIi16CY0C&printsec=frontcover |isbn=0199546045}}
Professor Manley's papers in the philosophy of language, metaphysics, and epistemology have appeared in such journals as ''Nous, The Journal of Philosophy, Mind'', and ''PPR''.
