{{Infobox language |name=Kumbewaha |nativename= |region=[[Buton Island]], [[Sulawesi]] |speakers=3,400 |date=2004 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[Celebic languages|Celebic]] |fam4=[[Muna–Buton languages|Muna–Buton]] |fam5=[[Buton languages|Buton]] |iso3=xks |glotto=kumb1274 |glottorefname=Kumbewaha }}
'''Kumbewaha''' (Umbewaha) is an [[Austronesian language]] spoken on [[Buton Island]] off the southeast coast of [[Sulawesi]] in Indonesia.
