{{Infobox language |name = Wayampipukú |states = Brazil |familycolor = American |fam1 = [[Tupian languages|Tupi]] | fam2 = [[Tupi-Guarani languages|Tupi-Guaraní]] | fam3 = Northern |iso1 = BR-Ap<ref>{{cite web|last1=Mouton|first1=De Gruyter|title=The Indigenous Languages of South America A Comprehensive Guide|url=https://amerindias.github.io/referencias/camgro12southamerica.pdf}}</ref> |linglist = 1az }} '''Wayampipukú''' is a [[Tupian languages|Tupian language]], more specifically, a Northern [[Tupi–Guarani languages|Tupi–Guarani language]].<ref name="multitree">http://multitree.org/codes/1az.html</ref> The language is very closely related to [[Wayampi language|Wayampi]].
